did.abstract: Addresses, programs, audio-visual recordings, and other materials documenting Stanford University commencement ceremonies

accessrestrict.head: Information about Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.
Audio-visual materials are not available in original format, and must be reformatted to a digital use copy.

userestrict.head: Ownership & Copyright
userestrict.p: All requests to reproduce, publish, quote from, or otherwise use collection materials must be submitted in writing to the Head of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, California 94304-6064. Consent is given on behalf of Special Collections as the owner of the physical items and is not intended to include or imply permission from the copyright owner. Such permission must be obtained from the copyright owner, heir(s) or assigns. See: http://library.stanford.edu/depts/spc/pubserv/permissions.html.
Restrictions also apply to digital representations of the original materials. Use of digital files is restricted to research and educational purposes.

prefercite.head: Cite As
prefercite.p: Stanford University Commencement Collection (SC1020). Dept. of Special Collections, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, Calif.

scopecontent.head: Description of the Collection
scopecontent.p: The materials consist of addresses, programs, audio-visual recordings, and other materials documenting Stanford University commencement ceremonies.

arrangement.head: Arrangement note
arrangement.p: The materials are arranged in four series: Series 1. Addresses; Series 2. Programs; Series 3. Audio-Visual Recordings; Series 4. Additional Material.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: VHS copy of 8mm film footage of the 1937 commencement in Frost Amphitheater and other campus scenes including Toyon and Branner Halls; persons on the tape include Mitchell, Melvin T. Hurley, Ralph Purdy, Ralph Qualls, Robert Schlenker, and Joseph Rhea.

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical note
bioghist.p: Thornton W. Mitchell earned his A.B. in history at Stanford University in 1937.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Video tape of the 1989 commencement activities. Includes the Baccalaureate service with speaker Jorge Lara-Braud, the class plaque ceremony, class day luncheon with talk by William Stone (president of the Stanford Alumni Association), commencement address by Garry Trudeau, and commencement remarks by Stanford University President Donald Kennedy.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: WEB DESCRIPTION Graduates engage in the Wacky Walk--a now traditional 30 minutes of performance art by graduates entering the stadium--which precedes the official ceremonies. Field tape shot list: Crowd Shots; Student Playing; Stanford Flag waving :30:00; Pillow fight 1:19; Bubbles 2:00; Paper dominos 3:00; Flower hats 4:10; Human Basketball hoop 5:00; Purple wigs 6:00; Beer Keg Drummers 6:10; Wacky Walk 7:00; Jump rope 8:15; Glitter wigs and dresses 9:50; Faculty walks in 10:00; Condoleezza Rice 13:40; Gerhard Casper 15:20; Condoleezza Rice takes the stage 16:10; Camera 2 has a better view of Condoleezza Rice. [Tape is labeled as: Townsend, Condi Reel TRT: 1:21, 48:00, 54:00, 1:00, 15:00, Hugs]
